Successful PC DBMSs can fund a similar amount of engineering as traditional server-oriented DBMSs. Thus, PC DBMSs could evolve quickly into powerful, yet easyto-use challengers to traditional DBMSs. Could a large number of PC DB servers compete with DBMSs designed for larger machines? In the medium-to-long term, what features will distinguish highend DBMSs? What fraction of DBMS market revenue will they have?